<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910506-0087</DOCNO><DOCID>910506-0087.</DOCID><HL>   Corporate Earnings Brief -- Data General Corp.:   Earnings Surprise: Up</HL><DATE>05/06/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   DGN</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)</RE><LP>   WESTBORO, Mass. -- Data General Corp. posted a fiscalsecond-quarter profit, its second consecutive quarterlyprofit, of $19.2 million, on a slight 1.8% increase inrevenue.   The computer maker's quarterly profit, equal to 60 cents ashare and more than twice the highest analyst estimate,reflects cost control measures and increasing sales of itsAviion line of industry-standard computers. The profitcompares with a year-earlier loss of $8.6 million, or 29cents a share. Revenue for the period rose to $320.4 millionfrom $314.8 million.</LP><TEXT>   Data General's results indicate that the company hasstabilized the decline in its MV (proprietary) line ofcomputers, which are used to run office automation systems,small businesses, refineries and factories.   Data General's results in the current quarter could behurt by several factors. The company's sale of its NipponData General unit will eliminate about $80 million in annualrevenue. And analysts have predicted that Aviion sales mayshow only modest growth in the current quarter.</TEXT></DOC>